@AnkitMishra3220 : Couple of things: 
1. If you are trying to ingest data directly in Hudi format, the "insert into" hive query will not work. You should instead use the delta-streamer spark-tool (or HoodieWriteClient API) as described in the quickstart : https://uber.github.io/hudi/quickstart.html#a-demo-using-docker-containers 
2. But (1) should not be the reason why are not seeing any data. Hudi input format allows non-hoodie partitions to be queried. Looking at the table definition, Are you sure the Location attribute is set correctly. I can see atleast one inconsistency - The table definition has location set as /user/hoodie-test wheres the hadoop fs queries points to /user/bdp/hoodie-test/...  Also, can you ensure the defaultFS is set to hdfs and not local fs. You can inspect the output of "desc formatted <table_name>" ?

@leletan : Yes this is intentional. The pom dependency (https://github.com/uber/hudi/blob/1628d044ac5b2197fd8a565961f68b3aa7936f67/hoodie-spark/pom.xml#L223)  also reflects that. We had added support to automatically sync partitions to hive when writing through DataSource API. 

